# load-data-job

# `load-data.sh` and `local-data-setup.sql`

`load-data.sh` and `local-data-setup.sql` sets up the local NetBox database (populate the required database tables, etc.) and demo data required to run the NetBox locally.

# Local demo data

For e2e tests and manual tests during development, we need more data inserted to the local NetBox instance.

## Using python VirtualEnv

For development setup
- Install virtualenv `brew install virtualenv`
- Create a new virtual environment `virtualenv netbox-operator`

For normal development (after the initial setup is done)
- source netbox-operator/bin/activate
- install `pynetbox` by executing `pip install pynetbox`

For more information, please read [this page](https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/latest/user_guide.html)

